TITLE: Feeling Consumers’ Pain, Retailers Bring Back Discounts
SUMMARY: The pandemic shopping boom led many stores and brands to widen profit margins by charging more. Now value is the watchword as shoppers grow choosier.

TITLE: Car Deals Vanished During the Pandemic. They’re Coming Back.
SUMMARY: Automakers and dealers are starting to offer discounts, low-interest loans and other incentives to lure buyers as the supply of cars grows.

TITLE: The Floating Traffic Jam That Freaked Us All Out
SUMMARY: The coronavirus pandemic schooled the world in the essential role of global supply chains. Have we learned anything from it?

TITLE: Alzheimer’s Takes a Financial Toll Long Before Diagnosis, Study Finds
SUMMARY: New research shows that people who develop dementia often begin falling behind on bills years earlier.

TITLE: U.S. Accuses Hyundai and Two Other Companies of Using Child Labor
SUMMARY: The Labor Department filed a lawsuit accusing Hyundai, one of its suppliers and a staffing company of jointly employing a 13-year-old on an auto body parts assembly line in Alabama.

TITLE: Why Are People So Down About the Economy? Theories Abound.

SUMMARY: Consumers eased up on spending in the face of rising prices and high interest rates, Commerce Department data shows.

TITLE: Will Billions More in New Aid Save Family Farms?
SUMMARY: The Biden administration aims to better support small farmers while still aiding big operations and rewarding climate-friendly practices. It’s a tall order.

TITLE: Home Insurance Is Clobbering Consumers. Yet It’s Barely Counted in Inflation.
SUMMARY: Skyrocketing premiums are hitting homeowners hard, but they barely factor into common price measures.

TITLE: If A.I. Can Do Your Job, Maybe It Can Also Replace Your C.E.O.
SUMMARY: Chief executives are vulnerable to the same forces buffeting their employees. Leadership is important, but so is efficiency — and cost-cutting.

SUMMARY: The Teamsters union has made little headway in organizing workers at Amazon and FedEx despite wage and other gains it secured at UPS last year.

SUMMARY: Western economic officials projected a united front, and braced for retaliation, as they prepped tougher sanctions and tariffs.

SUMMARY: A second Trump administration could shake up personnel and financial regulation at America’s central bank, people close to his campaign said.

TITLE: Fed Minutes Show Officials Were Wary About Inflation at May Meeting
SUMMARY: Federal Reserve policymakers were still willing to raise rates if the economy surprised them, notes from their most recent meeting suggested.

SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve’s 2023 survey on household financial well-being found Americans excelling in the job market but struggling with prices.

SUMMARY: Conflicting political visions, competitive jockeying and American dominance stand in the way of a more coordinated and efficient military machine.
